    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Removal - Valve Covers</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.2.1" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Valve Covers</title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s26504.2.1.1">
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death: Do not allow used engine fluids to stay on
                        your skin. Clean your skin and nails with soap and water, or a good hand cleaner. Wash or
                        properly throw away clothing or rags containing used engine fluids. Used engine fluids contain
                        certain elements that may be unhealthy for skin and could even cause cancer. See
                        <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, make sure that the engine has cooled down
                        sufficiently before attempting to remove any components. See
                        <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, disconnect the main battery negative
                        terminal before disconnecting or connecting any electrical components. See
                        <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <note>
                    <para>Engine fluids, oil, fuel and coolant, can be a threat to the environment. Never dispose of
                        engine fluids by putting them in the trash, pouring them on the ground, in the sewers, in
                        streams, or bodies of water.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s26504.2.1.3">
            <title>Right Valve Cover</title>
            <figure id="e300505" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Valve cover mounting bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen nine mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e300506" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the valve cover</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove valve cover.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Left Valve Cover</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Removing the crankcase vent hose assembly:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>CF series - Cut plastic tie straps securing hose to breather bracket, air cleaner bracket,
                            and chassis frame. Remove crankcase vent hose assembly from breather assembly. Remove O-ring
                            seal from hose elbow and discard.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Stripped chassis - Remove bolt (M10 x 16) anchoring hose to back of cylinder head. Cut
                            plastic tie straps securing hose breather bracket, and chassis frame. Remove crankcase vent
                            hose assembly from breather assembly. Remove O-ring seal from hose elbow and discard.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Unless the crankcase breather needs to be replaced, leave crankcase breather attached to left
                        valve cover.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="e300509" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08023.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the left valve cover with crankcase breather attached</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen nine mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove left valve cover with breather element attached.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the left valve cover gasket. Retain gasket for cleaning and inspection.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Breather Housing</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Remove the crankcase breather only when replacement is necessary. The left valve cover may be
                        removed without first removing the crankcase breather housing.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="e300507" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08021.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Valve cover and breather mounting hardware</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve cover bolt (9)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Breather bolt, M6 x 43 (6)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove six bolts that secure crankcase breather to the outside of the valve cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e300508" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08056.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the crankcase breather</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove crankcase breather from valve cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four breather opening seals.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The breather and seals are supplied as a service kit. Seals are not available separately.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s26504.2.1.5">
            <title>ICP Sensor and Gasket</title>
            <figure id="e300510" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the ICP sensor and gasket (right side)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">ICP sensor gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">ICP sensor</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the ICP sensor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove valve cover seal ring and retain for cleaning and inspection.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
